4.3.3 Evaluation
The CZ is an active participant in EUROCANET, while Germany has only a passive status.
From the standpoint of an active participant, it is unsatisfactory that other Member States refuse to participate.
Accordingly, the audit had to be carried out differently in this area.
But major differences in the success of UST fraud detection could not be found, because EUROCANET is only one component of the risk management system.
Both countries' fiscal administrations have a variety of other tools to detect fraudulent transactions.
The Council of the European Union agreed on draft regulation 13 establishing EUROFISC, a network to combat UST fraud.
The experience gained so far with EUROCANET should be shared and fed into this network by Member States at European level.
