5. Conclusions
Cooperation between the two courts of auditors has proved its worth.
Necessary insights have been gained into the systems used in both countries: in particular, intra-Community transactions, risk management at the UST, in particular with regard to the selection of high-risk transactions, UST claims recovery and UST auditing of large enterprises.
The audit laid bare differences in strategies for detecting UST fraud and in the systems explained above.
These findings can be used to improve existing procedures.
They can also be used to encourage stakeholders to discuss what audit approaches and strategies can be used to combat fraud, such as relations within and between Member States and the EU Commission.
The experience and insights gained should encourage the continued joint examination of the UST administration.
